latestIgtvVideos.title: Making of Kurkure momos!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A short video to show you guys how i made the crispy kurkure momos. Its super easy to make and tastes so good.
.
Prepare the momo dough and filling as usual.
For the dough, i have taken all purpose flour, refined oil, a pinch of salt and kneaded it with lukewarm water. For the filling, i have boiled the chicken with salt, black pepper powder and ginger-garlic paste. Shredded the chicken pieces and mixed it with finely chopped onion, chillies, coriander leaves. You can prepare a veg filling with different veggies like carrots, cabbage etc. or any filling of your choice.
.
Last step, Shape the momos, dip them in cornflour slurry, coat with crushed cornflakes and deep fry them. Prepare a red hot spicy chutney and enjoy!
.
Not a pro momo shaper..so please excuse the shapes😁
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Creamy Black Sesame Chicken~~
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
INGREDIENTS :
🔸500 gms Chicken
🔸2 onions, chopped
🔸5tsp black sesame seeds
🔸1tsp black peppercorns
🔸2 tsps ginger-garlic paste
🔸1 Tbsp cream
🔸1 bay leaf
🔸Salt, according to taste
🔸1-2 Tbsp Mustard Oil

RECIPE:
🔸First Marinate the chicken with mustard oil, ginger- garlic paste and salt, keep it for half an hour.

🔸Next dry roast black sesame seeds, black peppercorns. Make sure the seeds are not over roasted otherwise it will taste bitter. Now grind them to a fine paste adding little water and green chillies. You can add more green chillies if you want it more spicy.

🔸Now heat oil, add bay leaf, add the chopped onions and fry till golden brown. Next add the marinated chicken. Stir well and cover it to cook. 

🔸When the chicken is 80% done add the sesame paste and mix well. Add some hot water, cover and let it cook.

🔸When almost done, add the cream, you can garnish with coriander leaves. Serve hot.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Dear @foodieforeverandever23
Apple Coffee Cake without oven
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This Apple Cake is one of the most tried recipe from my feed. It was an experimental recipe but turned out really good. So many of you have tried and loved it, thought of saving it in my igtv.

INGREDIENTS :
🔸1 and 1/4th cup flour
🔸1/3rd cup semolina
🔸1 cup grated Apple
🔸1 tsp instant coffee
🔸1/2 cup melted butter
🔸1/3rd cup milk
🔸1 cup sugar
🔸2 eggs
🔸1 tsp baking powder
🔸1 tsp baking soda
🔸1/2 tsp salt
🔸1 tsp vanilla extract
🔸Dry fruits (optional)

RECIPE :
🔸Beat together butter, sugar and eggs until blended well.
🔸Whisk together flour, semolina, coffee, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add this to the sugar-eggs mixture and mix everything nicely.
🔸Add milk and blend it well.
🔸Add vanilla essence.
🔸Now add the grated apple and chopped dry fruits.
🔸Grease the baking tray with some butter and pour the batter.
🔸Bake it at 180°C for 35-40 minutes or you can even use pressure cooker or a big vessel which will take almost and hour.
🔸Insert a toothpick or tester at the centre, if it comes out clean its ready!
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Apple Rose
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Few days back when i posted the mango smoothie bowl, some of you wanted me to do a video on the making of the mango rose. I dont have mangoes on hand, so thought of sharing a video on apple rose.

Steps :
🔸Remove the core.
🔸Cut the apple in thin slices.
🔸Keep the slices in warm salt water for 5-6 minutes.
🔸Wipe the apple slices with a tissue paper.
🔸Place them one above another and roll it.
🔸You can add more slices if you want to make a bigger rose.
.
Video shot by @little_chef_tannu
